                            <comment id="471917" author="adilger" created="Thu, 18 Sep 2025 02:47:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It shouldn&apos;t be needed to unconfigure every interface manually when shutting down LNet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471685" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2025 19:31:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That means a LNet NI is still setup so it&apos;s refusing to shutdown LNet.&#160; Test 230 looks to be setting up several NIs and I bet it failed at some point without proper cleanup of the NIs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471676" author="adilger" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2025 18:30:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that this is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; failing on 2.16, so it seems possibly related to some recent change to Netlink/YAML?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
